
Setup --------------------

git config --global user.name "Your Name"   # Set your name for commits
git config --global user.email "you@email"  # Set your email for commits

Repository basics --------

git init                # Create a new local repository
git clone <url>         # Clone (download) a remote repo
git status              # Show changes in working directory
git log                 # View commit history

Staging and committing ------

git add <file>          # Stage a specific file
git add .               # Stage all changes
git commit -m "msg"     # Commit staged changes with a message

Branching --------------------

git branch              # List branches
git branch <name>       # Create a new branch
git checkout <name>     # Switch to branch
git checkout -b <name>  # Create and switch to a new branch
git merge <branch>      # Merge branch into current one

Remotes (Connected Repositories) --

git remote -v           # Show remotes (where repo is connected)
git remote add origin <url>  # Link local repo to remote
git remote remove origin     # Remove remote

Push and Pull ----------------------

git push origin <branch>     # Push branch to remote repo
git pull origin <branch>     # Fetch + merge changes from remote
git fetch                    # Fetch changes without merging

Undo and fix ------------------------

git restore <file>           # Undo changes in working directory
git reset HEAD <file>        # Unstage a file
git reset --hard HEAD        # Reset repo to last commit (⚠️ erases changes)
git revert <commit>          # Create a new commit that undoes a commit

Inspect ------------------------------

git diff               # Show unstaged changes
git diff --staged      # Show staged changes
git show <commit>      # Show details of a commit

